In this update:
[1] ASF spreads to a new county in Romania
[2] Belgium event, European alert

******
[1] ASF spreads to a new county in Romania
Date: Sun 16 Sep 2018
Source: Stiripesure (Romania) [edited]
https://www.stiripesurse.ro/first-african-swine-fever-outbreak-in-southern-dambovita-county_1289412.html


The southern County of Dambovita has recorded its 1st African swine fever [ASF] outbreak, and authorities have summoned the Local Centre for Combating Disease, AGERPRES Dambovita DSVSA (Sanitary Veterinary and Food Safety Directorate) director Sandu Tolea said on Sun 16 Sep 2018.

When asked about this outbreak, Tolea answered: "I cannot give you any further information since we are at a meeting of the Local Centre for Combating Disease."

The authorities were initially alerted after a local citizen lost 2 pigs to this disease.

On Thu [13 Sep 2018], the National Sanitary Veterinary Food Safety Authority (ANSVSA) announced that the ASF outbreak involves as many as 207 localities of 12 counties with over 898 outbreaks, out of which 13 are in industrial units, one in a farm's slaughterhouse, and another in an A-type commercial exploitation, and 57 cases in wild boars.

Overall, 232 722 pigs were culled since the date confirming the virus's presence in Romania, namely 31 Jul 2017, in the northern county of Satu Mare.

Satu Mare, Salaj, Bihor (northern Romania), Tulcea, Constanta, Braila, Ialomita, Galati, Calarasi, Ilfov, Buzau and Giurgiu (southeastern Romania) are the 12 counties affected by ASF.

The 1st ASF outbreaks occurred in January 2018 in 4 households of Micula commune, and they were eradicated on 13 and 24 Aug 2018, as was an outbreak in Sarauad, all in Satu Mare County.

The President of the Oversight Committee for the Romanian Intelligence Service (SRI), Claudiu Manda, on Friday [14 Sep 2018] stated that SRI head Eduard Hellvig maintained he had conveyed the 1st piece of information related to the danger of ASF to the legal beneficiaries in June 2016.

[Byline: Denisa Miron]

